OL,4,Cright' after Hillsborough Law
OL,5,Camendment pulled
OL,7,FThe mayor said: "It wouldn't have been
OL,8,Fa good thing to see the bill out in
OL,9,Fparliament today because this bill
OL,10,Fneeds solid agreement, cross-party but
OL,11,Falso from government, campaigners, and
OL,12,Fthe families.
OL,14,F"The amendment wasn't right in
OL,15,Frelation to the security services. It
OL,16,Fcreated too broad an opt-out. It gave
OL,17,Fthe head of services the right to
OL,18,Fdecide who would or wouldn't give
OL,19,Fevidence. That wasn't the spirit of
OL,20,Fthe Hillsborough Law.
OL,26,@oD@QOUvD@AOU
